Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and cut @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Using the tip of a #spoon{}, remove and discard black gills from undersides of @Portobello mushrooms{2}; cut into 1⁄2-inch-thick strips.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, juice from half the lemon, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{} until thoroughly combined (for 4 servings, use @sugar{1%tsp} and juice from whole lemon). Refrigerate until ready to use.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add another large drizzle of oil and mushrooms to pan. Season with half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp} (all for 4 servings), a pinch of salt, and pepper. Reduce heat to medium low and cover. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{3-4%minutes} (you may need to cook in batches for 4).

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @yogurt{2%tbsp}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.

Toast @pitas{2} until golden brown, then cut into quarters.

Divide veggies, @Sabra® Classic Hummus{4%tbsp}, salad, and pitas between plates in separate sections. Serve with white sauce on the side.

> TIP: Enjoy with your favorite hot sauce if you like things spicy!